ass the BS to get to where the raid is going on. <br><br>Like I said, I don't know much about CoTH, but if this is the real reason why they nerfed it in some zones, this seems a viable solution, and is virtually identical to the method they used with the Velious portal rings.<br><br> <p>Aldrin of the Nexus<BR><a href="http://www.xtimports.com/index.html"><img src="http://www.xtimports.com/data/Everquest/pics/Aldrinsig2.jpg" alt="Extra Terrestrial Imports " align="left" border="0" hspace="0" width="240" height="263"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samira>Samira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:04:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage CoTH</span><hr size=1> CotH doesn't work in several of the new Luclin dungeons. It's interesting that getting people into the dungeon to join your party was the whole point of the spell to begin with - but now they're saying that this allows players to bypass content. So it likely will be disabled in all the new dungeons at least.<br><br>I think of it as the &quot;manastoning&quot; of CotH. <br><br>Oh, well, at least they still have mod rods, right?<br> <p><img src=http://iseult.sidhe.freewebspace.com/images/samira.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uastralblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Astralblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:09:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage CoTH</span><hr size=1> People were bypassing doors that require keys.  It's like getting your mage a sleeper's tomb key and having him coth the rest of the guild in (yah it's not possible, but that's what it is on a smaller scale).  As far as the soulbound thing goes, you start to run out of inventory space pretty quick with soulbound keys. <p><img src="http://www.fnurt.net/~alex/pics/try2.bmp"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samira>Samira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:12:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage CoTH</span><hr size=1> So, implement a soulbound keyring.<br><br> <p><img src=http://iseult.sidhe.freewebspace.com/images/samira.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwuchild.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WuChild</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:32:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage CoTH</span><hr size=1> Now they said at fan faire that CoH &quot;should have never been added&quot;.<br><br>oh well<br><br>at least it still works in tov <p><a target="new" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9779>Maui's stuff</a> <BR> <a target="new" href=http://maui.freewebspace.com/photo.html>Maui himself</a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/unyalria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyalria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:43:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ow</span><hr size=1> &lt;picks at her scabs&gt;<br><br>CoH is disabled in Ssra Temple, Greigs End, Acrylia Caverns(not just disabled but DANGEROUS here), and The Deep.  Doesn't work in Plane of Sky either, and hasn't since shortly after Kunark came out.<br><br>A) One less reason to have a magi on a raid, and one less thing for a magi to do.<br>B) Terribly irritating to make sure every single person that needs to be there is there on time.  RL and EQ just dont work that way sometimes.  Waiting around sucks when people could be clearing to where we want to be.<br><br>Yes, it was being used to do things that ranged from shortcuts (keeping a wizard and magician camped somewhere hard to get to) to stuff bordering on exploiting to get a magician where they shouldn't be able to get and then CoHing the whole guild in.<br><br>I dare say a large part of the high-end, raiding magician community are rather displeased with their role, and Verant's apparent lack of concern/knowledge of the various problems magicians are having.  The CoH nerfs only adds to that, and causes everybody problems in the process!<br><br>Be nice to your magicians! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samira>Samira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:51:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1> Yes Mistress.<br><br> <p><img src=http://iseult.sidhe.freewebspace.com/images/samira.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uvokalkhords.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vokal Khords</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 12:43:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1> I'd like to see mages enhanced in other ways but I do agree that unchecked CotH is kinda gimpy. I'm glad they have zones it will not work in.<br><br>The mages have a serious case in that an xp farming chanter gets a better pet (by far) than a mage who has shed blood, sweat and tears for their epic. That is just flat-out wrong.<br><br>Vokal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubryhosugarfairy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bryho Sugarfairy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 5:22:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1> when you think about it, coth is a joke.  while i wasnt complaining during raids where we needed it, it really takes a lot away from the game, and should never have been put in<br><br>and no im not a vi employee <p><a href="http://www.pixyland.org/peterpan"><center><Img src="http://www.pixyland.org/peterpan/Imagezs/peter_flies1a_small.jpg"><br><b><u>Bryho Sugarfairy<br><i>*Retired*</i> 60 Warder</u></b></center></a href)</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugoddessr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess R</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 5:51:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1> I'm certain all my magician friends will love tohear that the one spell that made them wanted for raids has been nerfed. Kinda makes you wish verant would stop kissing up to the &quot;Holy trinity&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warmly Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 6:37:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1> They should take away ports next, because that allows people to &quot;bypass&quot; all of Verants hard work on all the zones in between where they are and where they are going.  <br><br>The whole thing with pets is kinda touchy, I would hate to see Enchanters/Bards ability to get charmed taken away from them, but I also am sympathetic to a Mage who does their Epic (which seems to be one of the longer ones to do, and Island 7!!!! of PoA).  After all that, they get to watch an Enchanter charm something that hits for 2-4 times as much as their Epic pets and has 5 times the HP.  I'll side with the Chanters on this one though, them charming something when a pull has gone bad many times has made the difference in living or dying.<br><br>How many of us have done Fay runs?  How many of you had to swim to the Island?  Heck no, everytime I've been there the majority of the people were CoTH'ed in.  How about late comers to Hate?  Too bad, you're out of luck now?  I see it as something like Ports for Druids or Mana spells for Necros that was a unique ability one class had that made them important/vital for raids.  It makes hunting in the Kael Arena or many other places so much better for when more Guildies show up or you need to replace someone.  With the see-invis stuff, it's not like they can get in there very easily.  Might as well take away FD from Monks, because people aren't using it in the way Verant intended.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utwansa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twansa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/30/02 11:22:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1>  Oh Well, at least I can solo...&lt;shrug&gt;<br><br><br>  Twansa Ponathyme<br>  50 mage<br>  Malu Morium <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uravantasuffer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravanta Suffer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 1:35:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~morbid909/morbidskull.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ow</span><hr size=1> CoH nerf is in a lot of ways, just as evil as nerfing summon corpse.<br><br>'What do you mean you can't summon my corpse Rav, you have a robe don't you?'<br><br>'Sorry babe, I have to go to the mystical safe spot in the zone in order to summon you'.<br><br>Do magicians complain about coh or lev being nerfed in plane of sky?<br><br>It would be VERY conveniant if the spells worked there.<br><br>But there are so many reasons why they don't.  This is all that VI is trying to say.  <br><br>I can think of a thousand reasons why coh would be nerfed in so many zones.  Now if you can tell me why DMF is nerfed in Katta, then you have my respect.<br><br> <p><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~morbid909/ezboardsig.jpg><br>Those who have turned away, shall be turned upon. <br>Ravanta Suffer 60 DE Necro Innoruuk </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/udalynia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalynia</A>&nbsp; <IMG 