ethe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 7:57:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Vison. Heh.</span><hr size=1> Actually, &quot;The Vision&quot; shouldn't exist any longer - that was a McQuaid/Butler thing, and doesn't explain anything.<br><br>I'd guess that lev/dmf is disabled in Katta, due to pathing issues. There's likely some sort of pathing flaw, that being lev'd would allow you to exploit. (Hrm, lev isn't disabled in Freeport, or Qeynos... /shrug)<br><br><br><br><br>-Daethe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uravantasuffer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravanta Suffer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 9:10:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~morbid909/morbidskull.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   They need to update there prescription.</span><hr size=1> The vision has changed a lot lately.  I remember they said dots would NEVER stack on a mob.  (2 different players casting the same dot)  Now they are saying they think it should, but don't know if they can get it to work.<br><br>I don't think it would ever go live, but if it did, it would definately empower dot classes.  They talk about wanting to change encounters away from the 'main tank' strategy, and I think that would only impair that vision.<br><br>Anyways, back to the magician issue with dire charm.  I'd like to point out a couple flaws dire charm has for sake of argument.  Some are small, some are quite large.<br><br>It's currently quasi-broken to where sometimes you can't get it to start casting on a mob.  (You get nothing but target is out of range, target is not undead, you have no target messages)<br><br>You can't tell when buffs wear off the pet such as haste.  Minor annoyance here, but if your in a situation where the pet does most of the damage, it can hinder you.<br><br>You can't use report health or taunt commands.  Small issue.<br><br>It only works on mobs below 46.  The only problem I have with the level restriction is that its a hassle determining if a mob is 46 or lower.  You can dire charm blues, but you need to find out if it is low enough level so you don't waste your dire charm on a mob thats to high.  Necromancers can do this by charming it with beguile undead, breaking charm, and then applying dire.  I'm sure enchanters and druids could do the same thing.<br><br>You can't use summon companion.  <br><br>If you somehow break charm on the mob, there is suddenly a hasted, dual wielding mob near you waiting to do some damage.  I've never been killed my own pet before, but I shudder to think of the situation where someone trains me and forces me to feign to avoid my own death.  <br><br>I certainly think a savvy magician who has the pet disclipline skill would be welcome to use there pet on most raids.  Even though personally I think the /hold command should be available by default.<br><br>I have fun with the skill, even though there are limited places where I can use it.  I would think an enchanter would be ALL OVER dire charm, especially since even there summoned pets they cannot control with pet commands.  But I wonder sometimes if a dire charmed mob really is stronger then the magician epic pet.  The damage shield on that pet is huge.<br><br>Wanna fight pets sometime Nyalria?<br><br><br><br> <p><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~morbid909/ezboardsig.jpg><br>Those who have turned away, shall be turned upon. <br>Ravanta Suffer 60 DE Necro Innoruuk </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/unyalria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyalria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 10:11:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: They need to update there prescription.</span><hr size=1> My pet, with DS and burnout 4, will probalby take out many 46 and below mobs. (It can take out as much as an annuled bok in sebilis)<br><br>Now if that same mob is enchanter hasted, and given two weapons to duel wield, I doubt it could.<br><br>Now, we have a class skill that, in theory, dramatically increases our pets damage output: 36 seconds of +100 atk, 100% haste, 100str, flurrys, rampages, and at the end a large AE nuke and then pet dies. The problem is:<br>a) it's broken in that it has the same problems as dire charm and manaburn - you use the skill on something that it should by all means work on, and it says target out of range, or that is not a pet, etc.<br>b) it's broken in that it doesn't make the pet &quot;suicide bomb&quot; bomb at the end. instead the pet just poofs.<br>c) debatably, it sucks =P<br><br>What it really should have been, and would have been useful would be 5 minute length (the skill can only be used every 72 minutes) and a much bigger increase in ATK so it can actually consistantly hit the uber mobs.  For those 5 minutes, that pet should be THE DEVIL INCARNATE (uber monk damage+), and then it can poof and go home, or better yet, just return to normal and not waste my time making a new pet.  For those 5 minutes, magicians would get to enjoy the awe they experienced pre50, pre-kunark: absolute offensive machine of doom.<br><br>Anyways, if I'm not dropping modrods somewhere, lets do some test runs, Ravanta. <p>Mistress <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5256>Nyalria</a><br>The Skittle Princess<br>Creator of Corpses<br>Legions of Darkness</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uvokalkhords.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vokal Khords</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 10:58:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: They need to update there prescription.</span><hr size=1> I'm just curious - do mages have any kind of skill or spell that makes their pets into ubertaunters for some short period of time? If not, wouldn't the awesome damage shield on their epic pets be useless in most groups? I'm thinking that the DS is what would allow the pets to take out most sub-46 mobs but make the pet inferior to dire charmed pets in most xp situations (damage out being key). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samira>Samira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 11:16:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: They need to update there prescription.</span><hr size=1> No, you can make the pet stop taunting and you can make it start taunting again but you can't make it taunt MORE than it does by default.<br><br>Beastlords can buff their pets with a proc/taunt effect, but I'm not sure how much that really adds to taunt. In any case it isn't available to other pet classes.<br> <p><img src=http://iseult.sidhe.freewebspace.com/images/samira.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utziarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tziarius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 11:49:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: They need to update there prescription.</span><hr size=1> The problem with pets being tanks is that if any pc is near the mob, the mob will always attack the pc. So that makes the pets taunting useless. I think thats how it works.<br><br>Tzi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samira>Samira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/31/02 12:05:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1038.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: They need to update there prescription.</span><hr size=1> Not quite. The mob will attack the nearest person or pet, depending also on who/what has built up more aggro. Pets tend to stand a little bit away from the mob, so players tend to get hit more.<br> <p><img src=http://iseult.sidhe.freewebspace.com/images/samira.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com